file_content.text: I was starting to think we'd have to finish without you.
Cut the garbage. I want an explanation.
I'm here, what do you want?
I can give you that much, but I don't like raising my voice. Keep walking.
Buddy, you've got no idea what you just got yourself into.
You're about to wish you had.
You don't say? Why don't you come a little closer and explain it to me.
Don't hold up on my account.
Ready when you are. [Draw out]
Ah, ah, ah. Keep walking.
Ambush, run!
You aren't saying anything your friend doesn't already know.
You know, Grand Champion, you've got talent. The overseers would have scouted you eventually.
We could have helped you make a real mark on the galaxy. Now you'll have to settle for your gaudy title and the price on your head.
Who are you working for?
Who's "we"?
We share a name you won't recognize. GenoHaradan. We solve the Republic's problems, remove troublemakers, keep things running smoothly.
Let him go before you do something you can't take back.
Last chance. Walk away.
You should really take your own advice.
Better than the mark you're about to make in the snow.
No complaints here, dead man.
Cocky and brutal. Just what I'd expect from Mandalorian scum.
Winning that Great Hunt really inflated your ego.
Bounty hunting isn't a game, whatever the Mandalorians think. It's serious business, with serious consequences.
Consequences you're about to become intimately familiar with.
